{"id":"1604.01757","submitter":"Markus Steindl","authors":"Markus Steindl","title":"On semigroups with PSPACE-complete subpower membership problem","comments":null,"journal-ref":"J. Aust. Math. Soc. 106 (2019) 127-142","doi":"10.1017/S1446788718000010","report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR cs.CC","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Fix a finite semigroup $S$ and let $a_1, \\ldots, a_k, b$ be tuples in a\ndirect power $S^n$. The subpower membership problem (SMP) for $S$ asks whether\n$b$ can be generated by $a_1, \\ldots, a_k$. For combinatorial Rees matrix\nsemigroups we establish a dichotomy result: if the corresponding matrix is of a\ncertain form, then the SMP is in P; otherwise it is NP-complete. For\ncombinatorial Rees matrix semigroups with adjoined identity, we obtain a\ntrichotomy: the SMP is either in P, NP-complete, or PSPACE-complete. This\nresult yields various semigroups with PSPACE-complete SMP including the\n$6$-element Brandt monoid, the full transformation semigroup on $3$ or more\nletters, and semigroups of all $n$ by $n$ matrices over a field for $n\\ge 2$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Apr 2016 04:41:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-20"}
